nadian filmmaker Guy Maddin. It offers extensive perspectives on his career to date, from the early experimentation of The Dead Father (1986) to the intensely intimate revelations of My Winnipeg (2007). Featuring new and updated essays from American, Canadian, and Australian scholars, collaborators, and critics, as well as an in-depth interview with Maddin, this collection explores the aesthetics and politics behind Maddin’s work, firmly situating his films within ongoing cultural debates about postmodernism, genre, and national identity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture producers and directorsxCanada. 0aMotion picture producers and directorszCanada. 0aProducteurs et réalisateurs de cinémaxCanada. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh1 aBeard, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChurch, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChurch, David, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCooley, Dana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEaston, Lee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHewson, Kelly, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMasterson, Donald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMatheson, Carl, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPevere, Geoff, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPike, David L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPribisic, Milan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShaviro, Steven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSnyder, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabular